    <statement><p>Simplify the following expressions, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{r+7}{r+7}}=}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{r+7}{7+r}}=}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{r-7}{r-7}}=}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0003"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{r-7}{7-r}}=}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0004"/></p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>1, r\ne -7</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>1, r\ne -7</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>1, r\ne 7</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-1, r\ne 7</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{    \begin{aligned}
    {\frac{r+7}{r+7}} \amp = {1, r\ne -7}
    \end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>r+7</m> was crossed out, <m>-7</m> is not in the domain. So the answer is <m>{1, r\ne -7}</m>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{    \begin{aligned}[t]
    {\frac{r+7}{7+r}} \amp = \frac{{r+7}}{{r+7}} \\
    \amp = {1, r\ne -7}
    \end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>r+7</m> was crossed out, <m>-7</m> is not in the domain. So the answer is <m>{1, r\ne -7}</m>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{    \begin{aligned}
    {\frac{r-7}{r-7}} \amp = {1, r\ne 7}
    \end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>r-7</m> was crossed out, <m>7</m> is not in the domain. So the answer is <m>{1, r\ne 7}</m>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{    \begin{aligned}[t]
    {\frac{r-7}{7-r}} \amp = \frac{{r-7}}{-(r-7)} \\
    \amp = \frac{1}{-1} \\
    \amp = {-1, r\ne 7}
    \end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>r-7</m> was crossed out, <m>7</m> is not in the domain. So the answer is <m>{-1, r\ne 7}</m>.</p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</solution>
